  => "Reference epilepsy implant comparator: NeuroPace RNS-300 (FDA approved 2013, 4 ch)"
  => "N1 N1 sampling/channel product = 256·80 = 20,480× raw data throughput vs RNS"

@F BRAINWIRE-AR-RNS-HFO-BLIND = RNS Nyquist=125 Hz blind to ripple HFO (80-250 Hz); N1 has 40× oversampling at 500 Hz :: hardware_comparison [10]
  <- verify_paper_p002_section_2_6
  => "RNS samples at 250 Hz → max detectable freq 125 Hz (Nyquist). Ripple HFO band"
  => "  reaches 250 Hz; fast-ripple reaches 500 Hz. RNS structurally cannot detect."
  => "Clinical implication: HFO-based seizure prediction infeasible on existing implants."

@F BRAINWIRE-AR-RNS-CLINICAL-DELTAS = RNS 53% (2yr) → 72% (9yr) seizure reduction; DBS-SANTE 69% (5yr); VNS 25-30% (1yr) :: clinical_baseline [10]
