// ── Section H — TECS-L verification framework (hypothesis hygiene) ──

@F BRAINWIRE-AR-TECS-L-RATING-RULES = "🟩 exact-proof | 🟧★ Texas p<0.01 | 🟧 p<0.05 | ⚪ p>0.05 coincidence | ⬛ falsified" :: hypothesis_hygiene [10]
  <- archive_brainwire_claude_md, brainwire_tecs_l_verify_py
  => "5-tier rating system applied across 145 hypotheses with mandatory:"
  => "  arithmetic-recheck → ad-hoc(+1/-1)-warning → small-number(<100)-warning →"
  => "  generalization-test (e.g. perfect number 28) → Texas Sharpshooter p (Bonferroni)"
  => "Forbidden: ⭐ before verification; 🟧+ without Texas test; ⭐ on +1/-1-corrected eq"

